Section 1:
HCR 30 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Committee Substitute House Concurrent Resolution 30 History OTHER VERSIONS  - Introduced Version | |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted Committee SubstituteforHOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION 30(By Delegates Toney and Vance)[Originating in the Committee on Energy and Public Works; Reported on March 20, 2025] Requesting the Division of Highways name Bridge Number: 55-009/04-006.66  () (55A028), (37.66467, -81.60096) locally known as COON BRANCH BRIDGE, carrying CR 009/04 over LAUREL FORK in Wyoming County, the "Pastor Roger D. Stewart Memorial Bridge."Whereas, Pastor Roger D. Stewart lived a life worthy of remembrance;Whereas, Pastor Stewart was born on October 19th, 1946, in Matheny, West Virginia, and passed away on April 30th, 2018; andWhereas, Pastor Stewart was the child of French and Lettie Stewart;Whereas, Pastor Stewart had a long career as a Pastor, serving in many churches, before retiring as the Pastor of the Campus Church of God in Cyclone, West Virginia; andWhereas, Pastor Stewart enjoyed singing with the Harless Family, evangelizing, and visiting with family and friends; andWhereas, Pastor Stewart is survived by his wife and partner in ministry Brenda Runion Stewart, son Mark (Cecilia) Stewart, daughter Kim (Shawn) Sanders, seventeen grandchildren, and numerous other family and friends; andWhereas, It is the wishes of the Stewart family that upon her death, Brenda Runion Stewart, be united with her husband, Pastor Roger D. Stewart; therefore, be it Resolved by the Legislature of West Virginia:That the Division of Highways name Bridge Number: 55-009/04-006.66  () (55A028), (37.66467, -81.60096) locally known as COON BRANCH BRIDGE, carrying CR 009/04 over LAUREL FORK in Wyoming County, the "Pastor Roger D. Stewart Memorial Bridge," and, be it Further Resolved, That the Division of Highways is hereby requested to have made and be placed signs identifying the bridge as the "Pastor Roger D. Stewart Memorial Bridge"; and, be itFurther Resolved, That upon the passing of Brenda Runion Stewart, the bridge shall be renamed the "Pastor Roger D. Stewart and Brenda Runion Stewart Memorial Bridge"; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Division of Highways is hereby requested to have made and be placed, at the time of Brenda Runion Stewart’s passing, signs identifying the bridge as the "Pastor Roger D. Stewart and Brenda Runion Stewart Memorial Bridge"; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk of the House forward a copy of this resolution to the Commissioner of the Division of Highways. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


